{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"enabled"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default, for every thread, is that they are enabled (as if called with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enabled"},{"type":"text","text":" being "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Those checks are conservative. That means that they will only succeed in considering a call thread-safe (and therefore allow it to happen) if the engine can guarantee such safety.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because of that, there may be cases where the user may want to disable them ("},{"code":"enabled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" being "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") to make certain operations allowed again. By doing so, it becomes the user’s responsibility to ensure thread safety (e.g., by using "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Mutex","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":") for those objects that are otherwise protected by the engine."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is an advanced usage of the engine. You are advised to use it only if you know what you are doing and there is no safer way.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is useful for scripts running on either arbitrary "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread"},{"text":" objects or tasks submitted to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkerThreadPool"},{"text":". It doesn’t apply to code running during ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node"},{"type":"text","text":" group processing, where the checks will be always performed."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even in the case of having disabled the checks in a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkerThreadPool","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" task, there’s no need to re-enable them at the end. The engine will do so."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets whether the thread safety checks the engine normally performs in methods of certain classes (e.g., "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":") should happen ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"on the current thread","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/thread\/setthreadsafetychecksenabled(_:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Type Method","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot6ThreadC03setC19SafetyChecksEnabledyySbFZ","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"title":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread\/setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Node":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Base class for all scene objects."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Node"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Node","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/node","title":"Node","role":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Mutex":{"title":"Mutex","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Mutex"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Mutex","abstract":[{"text":"A binary ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Semaphore","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for synchronization of multiple "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"s."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Mutex"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/mutex"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/WorkerThreadPool":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"WorkerThreadPool"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkerThreadPool","abstract":[{"text":"A singleton that allocates some ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread","isActive":true},{"text":"s on startup, used to offload tasks to these threads.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/workerthreadpool","role":"symbol","title":"WorkerThreadPool","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"WorkerThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Thread":{"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Thread"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/thread","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Thread","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread","abstract":[{"text":"A unit of execution in a process.","type":"text"}],"title":"Thread","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language."}],"title":"SwiftGodot","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","role":"collection","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Semaphore":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Semaphore","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Semaphore"}],"title":"Semaphore","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/semaphore","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Semaphore","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A synchronization mechanism used to control access to a shared resource by "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"s."}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Thread/setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/thread\/setthreadsafetychecksenabled(_:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets whether the thread safety checks the engine normally performs in methods of certain classes (e.g., "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node","isActive":true},{"text":") should happen ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"on the current thread","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread\/setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}]}}}